    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-09T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="468"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/740: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-09T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 9—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. 1. Following from Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 6, 3 p.m. Fifty percent ad valorem tax on cigarettes became
                            effective yesterday, pursuant to instructions from Nanking. Tobacco
                            companies have been paying 12½ percent. Request instructions whether
                            protest should be lodged. American companies Peking claim impossible to
                            continue business under this tax.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. Lockhart<note n="29" xml:id="d468fn29">Frank P. Lockhart, consul general at
                        Hankow.</note> authorized to lodge protest, if he considers it advisable,
                    bearing in mind the Department’s 278, July 7, 2 p.m., 1927.<note n="30"
                        xml:id="d468fn30">
                        <ref target="frus1927v02#pg_393">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1927, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 393</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
